By looking at Katniss' psychological state after shooting President Coin, we can see that the accumulation of her trauma left her with significant neurological damage, similar to the PTSD experienced by Vietnam Veterans.
This is important because the similarities shared in their feelings of depression, alienation, and anger result from betrayal by their respective governments.
