At her darkest hour, Katniss thinks to herself, "What I can do is give up.
I resolve to lie on the bed without eating, drinking, or taking my medications.
I could do it, too.
Just die" (Collins 375-376).
Despite her complete lack of desire to carry on, Katniss manages to survive her imprisonment.
